&lt;p&gt;
Effective altruism is an area of practical moral philosophy that extends the ideas of altruism, &lt;i&gt;i.e.&lt;/i&gt; selflessly doing good things for other people, 
to determine, through evidence and reason, &lt;b&gt;the most good you can do&lt;/b&gt; for other people. 
It combines both philosophy and the scientific method to determine the most effective way for an individual to improve the world
and gives compelling reasoning to incorporate this into their lifestyle.
&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Charity ain’t giving people what you wants to give, It’s giving people what they need to get.&lt;/p&gt;
